Following should help....

<dg:DataGrid x:Name="DataGrid_Standard" PreviewKeyDown="DataGrid_Standard_KeyDown" ...></dg:DataGrid>

        private void DataGrid_Standard_KeyDown(object sender, KeyEventArgs e)
        {
            if (e.Key == Key.Delete)
            {
                // raise an event before deleting the row
                if (DataGrid.DeleteCommand.CanExecute(null, DataGrid_Standard))
                {
                    DataGrid.DeleteCommand.Execute(null, DataGrid_Standard);
                }
                // raise an event after deleting the row
                e.Handled = true;
            }
        }

However, we will add this scenario to our internal database to be supported in future.
